@amihaiemil Seems like I can't work on this issue but I'm interested in its resolution so:

I've figured out the problem. `prerelease` is stored *as a string* in the `MkStorage`.

Therefore, this method in `Release.Smart` fails:

```java
        /**
         * Get a property as boolean.
         * @param name Parameter name
         * @return Returns boolean property value
         * @throws IOException If there is any I/O problem
         */
        private boolean booleanValue(final String name) throws IOException {
            return JsonValue.TRUE.equals(this.json().get(name));
        }
```

The part `this.json().get(name)` will return a `JsonString`, not a `JsonValue.TRUE`, and hence it will never be equal. That `JsonString`'s value will be the *string* `true` or `false`.

I'm not so sure what's the most elegant way to fix this.

@amihaiemil I think this simple hack should be ok:

```java
return Boolean.TRUE.equals(Boolean.parseBoolean(this.json().get(name).toString()));
```
